{"id":"51962965_Wave_Equation_Numerical_Resolution_A_Comprehensive_Mechanized_Proof_of_a_C_Program","abstract":"We formally prove correct a C program that implements a numerical scheme for\nthe resolution of the one-dimensional acoustic wave equation. Such an\nimplementation introduces errors at several levels: the numerical scheme\nintroduces method errors, and floating-point computations lead to round-off\nerrors. We annotate this C program to specify both method error and round-off\nerror. We use Frama-C to generate theorems that guarantee the soundness of the\ncode. We discharge these theorems using SMT solvers, Gappa, and Coq. This\ninvolves a large Coq development to prove the adequacy of the C program to the\nnumerical scheme and to bound errors. To our knowledge, this is the first time\nsuch a numerical analysis program is fully machine-checked.","authors":["Sylvie Boldo","Francois Clement","Jean-Christophe Filli√¢tre","Micaela Mayero"],"meta":["December 2011Journal of Automated Reasoning 50(4)","DOI:10.1007/s10817-012-9255-4","SourcearXiv"],"references":["267264045_AN_INTERVAL_METHOD_FOR_SOLVING_THE_ONE-DIMENSIONAL_WAVE_EQUATION","266550732_Hilbert's_'Verungluckter_Beweis'_the_first_epsilon_theorem_and_consistency_proofs","225142568_Z3_an_efficient_SMT_solver","222820289_SMT_2007_CCX_Semantic_Combination_of_Congruence_Closure_with_Solvable_Theories","221602471_The_ASTREE_analyzer","221302296_A_Generic_Library_for_Floating-Point_Numbers_and_Its_Application_to_Exact_Computing","221186669_A_New_Extraction_for_Coq","221186647_Constructive_Reals_in_Coq_Axioms_and_Categoricity","220992758_Towards_an_Industrial_Use_of_FLUCTUAT_on_Safety-Critical_Avionics_Software","51955722_Proof-irrelevant_model_of_CC_with_predicative_induction_and_judgmentalequality","51912020_Type_classes_for_efficient_exact_real_arithmetic_in_CoQ","47703835_Certifying_the_Floating-Point_Implementation_of_an_Elementary_Function_Using_Gappa","344487061_Special_Functions","321500999_Mechanics_of_